(17, 'Where To Buy: Air Jordan 1 “Homage To Home”', 'The Air Jordan 1 “Homage To Home,” a unique split design that draws inspiration from both the “Bred” Jordan 1s and the “Chicago” Jordan 1s, is set to see a full retail release this Saturday after a special Chicago-only version released last month. The two-piece colorway nods to the classic shoes themselves and 1985’s All-Star Weekend in Indianapolis where a rookie Jordan laced up both the “Bred” colorway to match his flight suit for the Slam Dunk Contest and the “Chicago” for the All-Star Game, marking the first and only time he would wear both shoes in a single weekend. He displayed both an air of confidence and an effortless swagger that were typically reserved for long-term NBA veterans, truly cementing his place as the next big thing in the NBA. The shoe is neatly split into two pieces by a long stitch down the middle, with the lateral side featuring all the black and red detailing of the Jordan 1 “Bred,” while the medial side trades the dark aesthetic of the Bred 1s for the “Chicago” Jordan 1’s classic red/white black color palate. A stately white Jordan 1 midsole and red outsole, used on both OG colorways makes for a middle ground that ties the split look together. Check out our comprehensive Where To Buy list for the “Homage To Home” Jordan 1s below for your best chance at getting your hands on a pair of the unique two-piece kicks.\r\n\r\nAir Jordan 1 Retro High OG\r\nRelease Date: May 19th, 2018\r\n$160\r\nColor: Black/White-University Red\r\nStyle Code: 861428-061', 1, '2018-05-15 00:00:00', '2018-05-03 00:00:00', 17890, 2, 'data:image/jpeg;base64,', 1, 2, NULL, NULL),
(9, 'Nike To Release Authentic And Swingman Michael Jordan Jerseys To Celebrate “Last Shot”', 'Jordan Brand is celebrating Michael Jordan’s famed “Last Shot” in a variety of ways – the most notable being the re-issue of the Air Jordan 14 worn during that epic Game 6. Today, the brand announces the release of an authentic version of the Chicago Bulls jersey worn during that historic final moment, as well as a Home and Away version of Nike’s Swingman jersey. All three jerseys will come equipped with NikeConnect technology which will unlock early content to the “Last Dance” Netflix documentary by ESPN, which is slated to debut in 2019. The authentic Chicago Bulls jersey is $400 and comes in a soft touch box with magnetic closure and clear window. The Swingman jerseys in Home and Away will retail for $120. The special-edition Bulls jersey also celebrates Friends of the Children, a national nonprofit that selects the most vulnerable children aged 4-6 from high-poverty schools and the foster care system and pairs them with a salaried, professional mentor who stays with them from kindergarten through graduation.\r\n\r\nNikeConnect Michael Jordan jersey\r\nRelease Date: May 31st, 2018\r\n$400 (authentic), $120 (swingman)', 0, '2018-05-18 03:25:00', '2018-05-18 00:16:00', 15067, 2, 'data:image/jpeg;base64,', 1, 2, NULL, NULL);

